Put a #large saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to the boil for the noodles. Slice each @British chicken thighs{4} into 1cm wide strips and place in a #mixing bowl{}. Sprinkle over the @Chinese five spice{¼%tsp}, mix well to coat the chicken, cover and set aside. Wash your hands, knife and #chopping board{} and then get on with the rest of your prep.

Halve, then remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and thinly slice. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{½}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced into half moons). Remove the root from the @spring onion{½}(root removed and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @ginger{½}(peeled and grated) and @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

Pop the @egg noodle nests{2} into your pan of boiling water and cook for ~{4%minutes}. Drain in a #colander{} and then run under cold water until they lose their heat.

> TIP: This is to stop them cooking anymore.

While your noodles are cooking, put a glug of @oil{glug} in a #large frying pan{} (or #wok{}) over high heat. Stir-fry the chicken until browned, ~{7-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If your pan is on the small side, cook the chicken in batches to make sure the meat doesn't stew.

When done, transfer the chicken to a #bowl{} and set aside.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add another splash of oil to your pan (if necessary) and lower the heat slightly. Stir-fry the pepper for ~{3%minutes}, then add the onion. Cook for another ~{2%minutes} and then add the chicken back into the pan. Add the ginger and garlic, cook for ~{1%minute} more before stirring in the drained noodles along with the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp} and @hoisin sauce{2%tbsp}.

Toss well, to make sure all the ingredients are combined and cook for another ~{1%minute} to ensure your noodles are piping hot. Finish the stir-fry by adding the spring onion and as much coriander as you like then serve immediately. Enjoy!